        q: `A 54-year-old woman has a long history of chronic hepatitis B infection and has had increasing malaise for the past year. Physical examination shows a firm, nodular liver, splenomegaly, and caput medusae. Laboratory findings show a serum albumin level of 2.5 g/dL (3.5–5.5 g/dL) and prothrombin time of 28 seconds (11–15 seconds). Which of the following complications is most likely to occur in this woman?`,
