        q: `A 27-year-old man develops malaise, fatigue, and loss of appetite three weeks after a meal at a seafood restaurant. He notes passing dark urine. On physical examination, he has mild scleral icterus and right upper quadrant tenderness. Laboratory studies show serum AST of 62 U/L (8–20 U/L) and ALT of 58 U/L (8–20 U/L). The total bilirubin concentration is 3.9 mg/dL (0.1–1.0 mg/dL). His symptoms abate over the next 3 weeks. On returning to the restaurant, he finds that the city’s health department has closed it. Which of the following serologic test results is most likely to be positive in this patient?`,
