        q: `A 42-year-old woman has had fever, chills, and bouts of colicky right upper quadrant pain for the past week. On physical examination, there is scleral icterus. Laboratory studies show a total serum bilirubin concentration of 7.1 mg/dL (0.1–1.0 mg/dL) and direct bilirubin concentration of 6.7 mg/dL (0.0–0.3 mg/dL). An abdominal ultrasound scan shows cholelithiasis and dilation of the common bile duct. Which of the following infectious agents is most likely to produce her symptoms?`,
