        optionFeedback: [`Ursodeoxycholic acid is used to treat primary biliary cholangitis. It reduces cholestasis and disease progression.`,`Liver transplantation is a last-stage option for patients with cirrhosis.`,`<!--Answers:-->The constellation of symptoms and signs in classic hereditary hemochromatosis are excessive absorption of iron from the gut with widespread deposition of iron. Liver involvement (causing cirrhosis), diabetes secondary to involvement of the pancreas, and cardiomyopathy with congestive heart failure are characteristic of this disease. Increased serum ferritin and iron deposits in the liver are diagnostic. The disease is hereditary but often manifests in middle age because the toxic effects of iron deposition tend to develop slowly. Phlebotomy is used to reduce the iron overload and is beneficial in preventing disease progression and improving cardiac function if the damage is not too severe. Reversal of other complications (e.g., diabetes, arthritis) is less commonly observed with phlebotomy therapy. `,`Prednisone is an anti-inflammatory drug that is not expected to be beneficial in this disease. Its utility is in treating autoimmune hepatitis.`,`Iron supplements would be harmful in this patient who already has iron overload `],
